messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /users/signin

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Individual HTTP methods (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: true
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The Express app mounts the router from routes/userRoutes.js at the prefix "/users" (index.js: app.use('/users', userRoutes)).
- In routes/userRoutes.js the signin handler is registered as router.post('/signin', signin). Combining the mount path and router path yields /users/signin and the route is registered only for HTTP POST.
- Therefore POST is explicitly acceptable (router.post).
- OPTIONS is marked true because index.js applies the cors middleware globally (app.use(cors())). The cors middleware handles CORS preflight requests and will respond to OPTIONS requests for routes it is applied to, so OPTIONS is effectively supported for /users/signin.
- HEAD is not explicitly registered. There is no GET route for /users/signin, so no explicit HEAD handling is present in the code; HEAD is therefore false.
- TRACE is not implemented anywhere in the code and Express does not register TRACE handlers by default, so TRACE is false.
- GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH are not registered for this path anywhere in the provided code, so they are false.
- "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false because only specific methods (POST and OPTIONS via cors) are supported per the code.
